{"Title":"ObjectCloud's Requirements","Contents":"\u003Cp>\u003Ca href=\"about.page\">About ObjectCloud\u003C/a>\u003C/p>\u003Ch1>Server-Side\u003C/h1>\u003Ch2>Windows\u003C/h2>\u003Cp>ObjectCloud requires the .Net framework, minimum version 2.\u003C/p>\u003Ch2>Linux and Mac\u003Cbr>\u003C/h2>\u003Cp>ObjectCloud requires Mono version 2.4 and SQLite.&nbsp; Most Linux distributions and Mac include SQLite, although you will need to download mono from \u003Ca target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.go-mono.com/mono-downloads/download.html\">http://www.go-mono.com/mono-downloads/download.html\u003C/a>.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch1>Web Browser\u003C/h1>\u003Ch2>Basic Requirements\u003Cbr>\u003C/h2>\u003Cp>ObjectCloud requires that the web browser support and enable cookies and Javascript.&nbsp; There are no plans to support non-Javascript browsers or to work without cookies.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch2>Browser Compatibility\u003Cbr>\u003C/h2>\u003Cp>The general philosophy of ObjectCloud is to stick with features that are well-supported on all browsers; however, browser compatibility is a moving target.&nbsp; Mozilla 3.5 and Safari 4.0 on Macintosh are currently the most-tested browsers.&nbsp; Additional testing is performed in Chrome.&nbsp; Internet Explorer 8 will have some display glitches and requires compatibility mode.&nbsp; Some pages require \u003Ca target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://http://code.google.com/chrome/chromeframe/\">ChromeFrame\u003C/a> when run with IE.&nbsp; Opera is untested.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>For this release, Mozilla 3.5, Safari, or Chrome is recommended.&nbsp; The long-term goal is to support all popular browsers, although some display glitches may exist in browsers that require high efforts for compatibility.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>ObjectCloud does not use Flash, Flex, or Silverlight although applications built on top of ObjectCloud might use them.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Ca href=\"about.page\">About ObjectCloud\u003C/a>\u003C/p>"}